        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:11PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 510 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ammon, or 10 miles northeast of Elizabethtown, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up 30 to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ammon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
